            <h2 class="section-heading">Agreement Between Cabocab and Drivers</h2>
            <p class="section-text">
                This Driver Agreement ("Agreement") is made and entered into by and between Raavanguard Private Limited
                ("Company"), and the individual driver ("Driver") who uses the Company’s online platform called as
                “Cabocab” to provide transportation services. This Agreement sets forth the terms and conditions under
                which the Driver will operate and provide services through the Company’s platform effective from 26th
                September 2024.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
            <h2 class="section-heading">1. Introduction</h2>
            <p class="section-text"><strong>1.1 Purpose:</strong> The purpose of this Agreement is to establish the
                terms and conditions governing the relationship between the Company and the Driver for the provision of
                transportation services.</p>
            <p class="section-text"><strong>1.2 Independent Contractor Status:</strong> The Driver acknowledges and
                agrees that they are an independent contractor and not an employee of the Company. This Agreement does
                not create an employer-employee relationship, partnership, joint venture, or agency relationship between
                the Company and the Driver.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
            <h2 class="section-heading">2. Definitions</h2>
            <ul class="terms-list">
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>2.1 Cabocab:</strong> An online taxi booking application that
                    connects passengers with drivers for transportation services created by Raavanguard Private Limited.
                </li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>2.2 Driver:</strong> An individual who has registered and been
                    approved to provide transportation services using the Cabocab platform.</li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>2.3 Cabocab Wallet:</strong> A digital wallet within the Cabocab
                    platform where the Driver deposits money in advance for operational purposes.</li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>2.4 Ride:</strong> The transportation service provided by the Driver
                    to a passenger, which is booked through the Cabocab platform.</li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>2.5 Service Fee:</strong> The fee charged by Cabocab for each
                    completed ride, which is 6% of the fare including GST.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
            <h2 class="section-heading">3. Eligibility and Registration</h2>
            <ul class="terms-list">
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>3.1 Eligibility Requirements:</strong> The Driver must meet the
                    following requirements to be eligible to use the Company's platform:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Hold a valid driver’s license, Aadhar card, Pan Card, Registration Certificate.</li>
                        <li>Own or have access to a vehicle that meets the Company’s standards.</li>
                        <li>Pass a background check and vehicle inspection as required by the Company.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>3.2 Registration Process:</strong> The Driver must complete the
                    registration process on the Company’s platform, which includes providing accurate and complete
                    information, agreeing to this Agreement, and fulfilling all eligibility requirements.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
            <h2 class="section-heading">4. Scope of Services</h2>
            <p class="section-text"><strong>4.1 Provision of Services:</strong> The Driver agrees to provide
                transportation services to passengers who book rides through the Cabocab platform.</p>
            <p class="section-text"><strong>4.2 Non-Exclusivity:</strong> This Agreement is non-exclusive. The Driver is
                free to provide transportation services through other platforms or independently, provided that such
                activities do not interfere with the obligations under this Agreement.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
            <h2 class="section-heading">5. Cabocab Wallet</h2>
            <ul class="terms-list">
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>5.1 Establishment of Wallet:</strong> Upon registration and
                    approval, the Driver will establish a Cabocab Wallet within the Cabocab platform.</li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>5.2 Initial Deposit:</strong> The Driver agrees to deposit an
                    initial amount of [Minimum Rs. 100] into the Cabocab Wallet before commencing any rides and maintain
                    this amount.</li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>5.3 Recharging the Wallet:</strong> The Driver is responsible for
                    ensuring that there are sufficient funds [Minimum Rs. 100] in the Cabocab Wallet to acquire rides
                    and cover the Service Fees for completed rides. The Driver agrees to recharge the Wallet as
                    necessary.</li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>5.4 Automatic Deductions:</strong> Cabocab will automatically deduct
                    the Service Fee (5% of the fare including 18% GST of the 5% acquired as GST) from the Driver's
                    Cabocab Wallet upon the completion of each ride.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
            <h2 class="section-heading">6. Services Provided by the Driver</h2>
            <p class="section-text"><strong>6.1 Provision of Services:</strong> The Driver agrees to provide
                transportation services ("Services") to passengers ("Riders") who request rides through the Company’s
                platform. The Driver has sole discretion over the means and methods of performing the Services.</p>
            <p class="section-text"><strong>6.2 Service Standards:</strong> The Driver agrees to maintain the following
                standards while providing Services.
            <ul>
                <li>High standards of professionalism</li>
                <li>Courtesy</li>
                <li>Safety</li>
                <li>Drivers agree not to use the platform for any illegal or unauthorized purpose.</li>
                <li>Drivers must respect the user and not be abusive.</li>
                <li>Driver must not be intoxicated and should be of sound mind while providing the service.</li>
            </ul>
            </p>
            <p class="section-text">The Driver must comply with all applicable laws, regulations, and Company policies.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
            <h2 class="section-heading">7. Use of the Company’s Platform</h2>
            <p class="section-text"><strong>7.1 Access to the Platform:</strong> The Company grants the Driver a
                limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable right to access and use the Company’s platform to provide
                Services.</p>
            <p class="section-text"><strong>7.2 Account Security:</strong> The Driver is responsible for maintaining the
                confidentiality of their account credentials and for all activities that occur under their account.</p>
            <p class="section-text"><strong>7.3 Prohibited Activities:</strong> The Driver must not engage in any
                fraudulent, illegal, or harmful activities while using the Company’s platform. This includes, but is not
                limited to, misrepresenting information, accepting unauthorized payments, or endangering the safety of
                Riders.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
            <h2 class="section-heading">8. Financial Terms</h2>
            <ul class="terms-list">
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>8.1 Service Fee:</strong> Raavanguard will deduct a Service Fee of
                    5% with 18% GST of the 5% fee from the fare of each completed ride. This fee will be automatically
                    deducted from the Driver's Cabocab Wallet.</li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>8.2 Payment to Driver:</strong> Raavanguard is not responsible for
                    the payment to Drivers. Drivers will receive their earnings directly from passengers either through
                    UPI ID or by cash.</li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>8.3 Refunds and Chargebacks:</strong> In the event of a refund or
                    chargeback, Cabocab reserves the right to deduct the relevant amount from the Driver's Cabocab
                    Wallet. Please refer to the Refund Policy for more information.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
            <h2 class="section-heading">9. Insurance</h2>
            <p class="section-text"><strong>9.1 Driver’s Insurance:</strong> The Driver must maintain valid auto
                insurance coverage that meets or exceeds the minimum legal requirements in their jurisdiction. The
                Driver must provide proof of insurance to the Company upon request.</p>
            <p class="section-text"><strong>9.2 Company’s Insurance:</strong> The Company may provide supplementary
                insurance coverage for certain incidents while the Driver is providing Services. The terms and
                conditions of such coverage will be communicated to the Driver.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
            <h2 class="section-heading">10. Term and Termination</h2>
            <ul class="terms-list">
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>10.1 Term:</strong> This Agreement will commence on the date first
                    written above and will continue until terminated by either party in accordance with this Agreement.
                </li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>10.2 Termination by Driver:</strong> The Driver may terminate this
                    Agreement at any time by providing written notice to Cabocab.</li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>10.3 Termination by Raavanguard:</strong> Raavanguard may terminate
                    this Agreement immediately for any reason, including but not limited to the Driver's breach of this
                    Agreement, poor performance, or misconduct.</li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>10.4 Effect of Termination:</strong> Upon termination, the Driver
                    must cease using the Cabocab platform and remove the Cabocab application from their device. Any
                    remaining balance in the Cabocab Wallet will be refunded to the Driver, minus any outstanding
                    Service Fees or other charges, as per the Refund Policy.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="terms-section">
            <h2 class="section-heading">11. Penalty</h2>
            <p class="section-text">To ensure safety, professionalism, and quality service, all Cabocab drivers are
                required to adhere to the driver responsibilities outlined in the Terms and Conditions. Non-compliance
                with these Service standards will result in penalties:</p>
            <ul class="terms-list">
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>11.1 Canceling rides frequently without valid reasons:</strong> The
                    driver will be provided a maximum of 3 cancellations in any particular day. Frequent cancellation of
                    rides will result in much lesser ride allocation during the day.</li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>11.2 Severe violations:</strong> (e.g., driving under the influence,
                    assault, or serious misconduct): Immediate account deactivation and permanent termination of the
                    driver’s access to the platform upon investigation. Additionally, a huge penalty will be applied
                    depending on the seriousness of the offense.</li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>11.3 Passenger complaints:</strong> regarding rude behavior or
                    unsafe driving: The driver will be investigated upon receiving multiple allegations from different
                    users. The result of the investigation is final and binding.</li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>11.4 Repeated offenses:</strong> Upon receiving 3 severe warnings
                    within a 30-day period, the driver's account will be temporarily suspended for up to 14 days.</li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>11.5 Final Decision:</strong> Cabocab reserves the right to make the
                    final decision regarding the enforcement of penalties. Continued violations or failure to comply
                    with penalties may result in permanent account deactivation and a ban from rejoining the platform.
                </li>
                <li class="terms-list-item"><strong>11.6 Appeal Process:</strong> Drivers have the right to appeal any
                    penalties imposed by submitting an appeal through the Cabocab Driver Support Portal within 7 days of
                    the penalty notification. The decision taken after the investigation following the appeal process
                    will be final and binding.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

